Robert F. URBANO, Appellant, v. Richard J. HUGHES, Governor of the State of New Jersey, Lloyd W. McCorkle, Commissioner of Institutions and Agencies of the State of New Jersey, Howard Yeager, Principal Keeper of the New Jersey State Prison, Board of Managers of the New Jersey State Prison, and Their Agents. No. 15334. United States Court of Appeals Third Circuit. Submitted Nov. 15, 1965. Decided Nov. 30, 1965. Robert F. Urbano, pro se. Eugene T. Urbaniak, Trenton, N. J. (Arthur J. Sills, Atty. Gen. of New Jersey, on the brief), for appellees.

Before KALODNER, Chief Judge, and McLAUGHLIN and SMITH, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On review of the record we find no error. The Order of the District Court will be affirmed.
